stateDiagram-v2
    %% Machine à états autoritaire du moteur backend (crate game-logic)
    %% engine::GamePhase = Idle | InGame | GameOver, avec sous-états PvE.

    [*] --> Idle

    Idle --> InGame : StartGame

    state InGame {
        [*] --> WaitingForScore
        WaitingForScore --> Fighting : seuil de score atteint (boss spawn)

        Fighting --> Fighting : BumperHit / ComboActivated / UltimateActivated / BallSaved / LifeUp
        Fighting --> Fighting : TiltDetected (pénalité -2000 puis -6000)
        Fighting --> Cheating : 3e Tilt → cheating_detected
        Cheating --> Fighting : score gelé (add_score ignoré)

        Fighting --> Cooldown : BossDefeated (animation de mort)
        Cooldown --> WaitingForScore : boss suivant (current_boss_index++)
        Cooldown --> Victory : dernier boss vaincu / endless_level++
    }

    InGame --> GameOver : GameOverTriggered (NoLivesLeft)
    InGame --> GameOver : GameOverTriggered (PlayerQuit)
    Victory --> GameOver : EndGame

    GameOver --> Idle : rejouer / attract
    GameOver --> [*]

    note right of InGame
        L'UI back_screen reflète un sous-ensemble :
        idle → mode_select → character_select →
        playing ⇄ paused → game_over
        L'ESP32 reçoit ces phases via game/state (retain).
    end note

